cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DB

This paper deals with the task of fine-grained entity typing, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel framework for embedding entities and types into a low-dimensional space, which is a machine learning technique that falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of knowledge bases, which is related to the field of cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper deals with the task of identifying correct type labels, which is related to the field of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
